<HEADLINE>
STRICKLAND GETS CHANCE WHILE PACK IS SIDELINED
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DWAIN PRICE 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   DALLAS _ He was planted at the end of the bench early in the
season, then placed on the injured list, and had become the
Mavericks' forgotten guard.
</P>
<P>
   But with Robert Pack sidelined two to four weeks with a slightly
torn right hamstring, Erick Strickland's importance to the
Mavericks has increased immensely, coach Don Nelson said.
Strickland and Hubert Davis can expect to play more minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Seizing the moment, Strickland scored 13 points in 11 minutes
during Monday's 106-91 loss to Portland. The third-year guard made
5 of 8 shots from the field and collected two assists and two
rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm pleased that I got back to my aggressiveness, attacking
and pushing the ball,'' Strickland said. ``They mostly have been
playing me at (shooting guard) lately, but I took it upon myself to
get the ball more and push it and try to create shots for the other
guys.''
</P>
<P>
   Strickland didn't play in 15 of the Mavericks' 23 games,
including the four games before Monday.
</P>
<P>
   That's why Nelson sounded pleased about Strickland's performance
against the Trail Blazers.
</P>
<P>
   ``Erick Strickland stepped up, without playing for a long time,
and played a very fine game,'' Nelson said. ``So, good for him.''
</P>
<P>
   With Pack out, Strickland knows this is an opportunity to show
the coaching staff what he can do.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think if I go in and be solid I may get more of a chance to
play,'' he said. TRENT THANKFUL
</P>
<P>
   Gary Trent, who is scheduled to become a free agent July 1, has
said he will strongly consider re-signing with the Mavericks. His
agent is echoing those sentiments.
</P>
<P>
   ``Gary's really wanted to be in a situation where he can get
some playing time and be with an organization that appreciates what
he can do as a frontline player,'' agent Mark Termini said. ``It
looks like this situation is evolving into that, and that's real
big in our minds.
</P>
<P>
   ``So everything is very positive as far as the Dallas situation
goes. But no decisions have been made either way, and certainly no
doors have been closed about Gary coming back to Dallas.''
</P>
<P>
   Under the NBA's collective bargaining agreement, the most the
Mavericks can offer Trent is a one-year, $2 million contract.
Mavericks officials said they expect five or six teams to be under
the salary cap this summer, and any could offer Trent a more
lucrative long-term contract. EXTRA WORK
</P>
<P>
   Nelson gave every player Tuesday off except Samaki Walker, Chris
Anstey and Dirk Nowitzki. Those three players were first-round
draft picks the past three seasons. nn
</P>
</TEXT>
