a viable treatment _ is in the works, thanks to the discovery of a
molecule known as ICAM-1. Find out the compelling story of the
scientists whose discoveries may soon wipe out runny noses and
hacking coughs in this feature by Gary Taubes, a contributing
editor at Discover magazine. Taubes won the 1997 Pan American
Health Organization award for excellence in international health
reporting.
