<P>
   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ Science takes a back seat to the supernatural
when credit for NASCAR Winston Cup victories is handed out, at
least by NASCAR champion Jeff Gordon, who seems to win most of the
races. This habit of giving thanks to God for winning another pile
of money doesn't sit too well with the other two dozen or so
drivers who, by implication, were not as deserving of God's divine
intervention as was Gordon. (Nethaway, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
