Eric Meuth lifted his arms over his head like he'd just wrestled a
bull to the ground at the rodeo. And no wonder. Meuth had just run
a floor buffer through the twisting buffer driving course without
knocking over any peanuts Tuesday at The Custodial Tournament of
Champions VII. This year Southwest Texas State dusted the
competition to win the traveling trophy for the first time. (Kelso,
Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
