The grandson of R.J. Reynolds has testified against the tobacco
industry before Congress. That's an easy audience compared with
what he faced at Dayton's Kettering Middle School: 400
sixth-graders, squirming in an auditorium, ready for him. (McCarty,
Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
