<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TV-C-SPAN-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
C-SPAN MARKS ITS 20TH ANNIVERSARY 
</HEADLINE>
   TV Notes  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By TIM GOODMAN  
 c.1999 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ History is being made on Friday: the 20th
anniversary of C-SPAN.
</P>
<P>
   You can use trusty old C-SPAN as the butt-end of a bad joke. But
not here. We know C-SPAN for what it truly is _ the country's most
underappreciated network.
</P>
<P>
   The handful of people who watch MSNBC can talk all they want
about news coverage. The people at Fox News can spin the media _
their own company excluded, of course _ as politically biased.
</P>
<P>
   But there's only one truly unfettered source for finding out
exactly how the political machine works in this country and it's
C-SPAN.
</P>
<P>
   If we weren't such a bored culture, thirsting for MTV quick cuts
and Sam Donaldson's squint as he gets all pedantic ``analyzing''
the news, then we'd watch C-SPAN and soak up American political
history as it happens.
</P>
<P>
   So many people were stunned to find out exactly how inept,
insipid and biased the Congress really was amid all the coverage of
President Clinton's sex scandal, but veteran C-SPANers were
nonplused. They'd seen how low we could go a long time ago.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   It was revealed on ``Good Morning America'' that Muhammad Ali's
21-year-old-daughter, Laila Ali (in her first TV interview), is a
boxer. Did everyone else sleep through this? Missed it and regret
it. Did she work Charlie Gibson like a heavy bag? Is there a
21-year-old Georgette Foreman out there? Will there be a
pay-per-view event?
</P>
<P>
   Let this be a lesson: Sleep through the morning shows and you
know nothing, friend. Nothing.
</P>
<P>
   And where was Oprah during this revelation?
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Daytime smut peddlers like Jerry Springer have been written
about and derided so much that now everyone has given up, as the
horse is now apparently dead and well beaten.
</P>
<P>
   But we're not done. We're inspired by Laila, baby. We're
throwing roundhouses, angry as Mike Tyson off his lithium or
whatever. We're not going to let Ricki Lake _ smut peddler
extraordinaire _ get away with these real-life topics: ``Girl, It's
Gonna Get Heated ... I've Got Proof Your Man Cheated''; ``You
Treated Me Badly ... Today You Pay!'; ``Wake Up, Girl! He's Told
You He's Gay ... Why Do You Stay?''; ``You Made a Mess ... Today I
Force You to Confess Your Secret!''
</P>
<P>
   And, finally: ``Fasten Your Seatbelts ... Today We'll Replay the
Best Battles From the Past.''
</P>
<P>
   And that's only a week's worth. Maybe Ricki Lake is at peace
with herself about getting rich off the backs of ignorant America,
but we're hoping there's some serious Instant Karma coming up.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The people at Imagine Television _ the powerful producing group
formed by Ron Howard and Brian Grazer _ wants to create an
African-American competitor to Barbara Walters' ``The View.'' They
are calling it ``Girlfriends'' and have Robin Givens and Kym
Whitley lined up. They are looking for a younger black female to
get the twentysomething crowd.
</P>
<P>
   Not to be territorial here, but isn't there really a show like
this already, except it has only one ``Girlfriend. '' That's right
_ ``Oprah.''
</P>
<P>
   Don't wake the sleeping giant.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
