   RUSSIA-PROSECUTOR (Moscow) _ In direct challenge to President
Boris Yeltsin, the upper house of Parliament votes to reverse his
firing of Russia's chief prosecutor, Yury Skuratov, who had
``resigned'' last month allegedly on health grounds. Wednesday's
vote was the latest chapter in a long-running saga, extraordinary
even by Russian standards, of Kremlin intrigue, high-level
corruption, blackmail and alleged sexual misconduct. By Celestine
Bohlen.
