   MEDICARE-ASSESS (Washington) _ A news analysis on the failure of
the commission headed by John Breaux to find a solution for
restructuring Medicare, after the earlier failure by Ira Magaziner,
architect of the Clintons' ill-fated health care plan. They both
shared what might be called the hubris of health care reformers:
the belief that they could devise an all-encompassing scheme to
redesign a huge swath of America's health care system. Both failed
spectacularly, and their efforts suggest that piecemeal incremental
changes are the best that Congress can do given the political and
technical complexity of the subject. By Robert Pear.
</P>
