   SCI-MARIJUANA-HEALTH (Washington) _ The most comprehensive study
of the health benefits of marijuana has found that the active
components of the drug are potentially effective in treating pain,
nausea, and the severe weight loss associated with AIDS, and
recommends that the government sponsor research. By Sheryl Gay
Stolberg. (1100 words)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-HEARTBURN-CANCER (Undated) _ Chronic heartburn can greatly
increase a person's risk of developing one of the deadliest of
cancers, adenocarcinoma of the esophagus, a major new study has
shown. Having chronic heartburn _ which results when the acidic
contents of the stomach back up into the esophagus _ increased the
risk of cancer by nearly eight-fold. And among patients with
long-standing, severe heartburn, the risk of developing esophageal
cancer was 43.5 times as great. By Jane E. Brody. (1200 words)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-BALLOONISTS (Undated) _ The balloonists Bertrand Piccard and
Brian Jones headed out over the Caribbean on Wednesday looking well
on track to complete the first non-stop balloon flight round the
world this weekend. By Malcolm W. Browne. (800 words)
