points, or 0.8 percent. Elsewhere, prices rose 1.2 percent in Tokyo
and 0.3 percent in Hong Kong. They fell 0.6 percent in Frankfurt,
0.8 percent in London, 0.8 percent in Brazil and 0.7 percent in
Mexico. On the American debt market, the long bond was down 8/32
point, with the yield at 5.49 percent. By Robert D. Hershey.
