<SLUG> BC-GRIMES-HUMOR-COLUMN-$ADV19-NYTR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
REWARDING POOR HOUSEKEEPING 
</HEADLINE>
   (For release Friday March 19)  
(rk) 
 By DAVID GRIMES   
 Sarasota (Fla.) Herald-Tribune   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   As you no doubt were, I was outraged to read that the government
of Israel rewards women for being lousy housewives.
</P>
<P>
   Israeli housewives cannot collect government disability checks
unless they demonstrate incompetence in a variety of tasks,
including mopping the floor, ironing and slicing bread.
</P>
<P>
   Housewives who fail the tests are eligible for a disability
pension of about $400 a month, according to a story by The
Associated Press.
</P>
<P>
   What irks me about this program is that it does not apply to
men.
</P>
<P>
   Men are just as capable of being lousy housekeepers as women, I
don't care what the Israeli government or Gloria Steinem says. In
fact, from what I've observed, men are superior to women in almost
every aspect of shoddy housekeeping. Laundry, vacuuming, making
beds _ we stink at all of it.
</P>
<P>
   A man's idea of proper housekeeping is pitching his empty beer
cans in the direction of the trash can. (Fussy men hang those
little plastic basketball hoops above the can.) A woman's idea of
proper housekeeping is ironing the toilet seat cover or arranging
the spice cabinet in alphabetical order.
</P>
<P>
   A college campus is a good place to visit if you want to get a
sense of the yawning gap in housekeeping skills between men and
women. Put one woman, alone, in a dormitory room and the result is
a clean room. Put two women in there and the room is cleaner still.
Add a third woman and you're talking about the kind of sterile
environment normally associated with hospital operating rooms.
</P>
<P>
   Put one man, alone, in a dormitory room and you've got a health
hazard. Two, and you've got an epidemic; three and the only
solution is to evacuate the area and bury the entire dormitory
under three feet of concrete like they did with the damaged
Chernobyl reactor.
</P>
<P>
   If college men were rewarded for their slovenliness, they would
not have to worry about passing chemistry or staying awake during
the economics lecture. They would make a good income simply from
their ability to carpet their rooms in pizza boxes and go an entire
semester without doing laundry.
</P>
<P>
   There is, of course, a downside to offering government checks to
men who are lousy housekeepers. For one thing, the government would
immediately go bankrupt.
</P>
<P>
   Another problem would be coming up with an incompetency test
that is fair to both men and women. In one of the Israeli
housekeeping tests, an evaluator threw sand on the kitchen floor
and watched as the housewife swept it up. If she did a poor job of
sweeping it up, she got money. If she did a good job, she got
nothing.
</P>
<P>
   This test would not work for men, who would see a layer of sand
as an improvement over whatever was sticking to the floor before.
Instead of reaching for the broom, the man would ask for more sand.
He might even invite a couple of his college roommates over to help
throw sand in other rooms in the house. Then they would all sit
down and have a beer, neatly throwing their empties in the
direction of the sand-filled trash can.
</P>
<P>
   Should men receive government disability checks because they are
lazy, worthless louts who enjoy living like swine?
</P>
<P>
   That is a tough call.
</P>
<P>
   All I can say is that as a sensitive, enlightened, '90s, giving,
sharing, caring American male, I do not expect to be rewarded for
being a pig. I am glad to provide this service free of charge. If
you are looking for someone who will not iron, will not dust but
will clip his toenails over the coffee table, then I am your man.
</P>
<P>
   Don't even think of trying to pay me, because I won't accept it.
</P>
<P>
   Though if you'd adjust the backboard behind the trash can, I'd
appreciate it.
</P>
<P>
   (David Grimes is a columnist for the Herald-Tribune in Sarasota,
Fla.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
