</P>
<P>
   DOW-FOURK _ Ordinary Americans, saving slowly and diligently for
their retirement years, helped push the Dow to 10,000 Tuesday.
Retirement accounts such as 401(k) plans now hold close to $1.4
trillion worth of stocks, or a 10th of the total value of U.S.
stocks. Add to that the stock investments in individual retirement
accounts and traditional pension plans, and the total shoots to an
estimated 30 percent of the total market value. (Ezell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   DOW-WOMEN _ Women are claiming a stronger presence among
financial investors. (Luke, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
