</P>
<P>
   NFL-OWNERS-NOTES _ PHOENIX _ Notes from NFL owners meeting.
(Pasquarelli, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   FBN-IFL-WINSLOW _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Mention the name Kellen Winslow
to football fans of a certain age and a clear image leaps to mind
of this player, completely spent, white towel draped over his head,
being assisted from the field by two teammates. He had just driven
the San Diego Chargers past the Miami Dolphins, seemingly with
every fiber of his existence. Nary a day passes when he isn't
reminded of that Jan. 2, 1982 overtime playoff game. ``Good thing
we won,'' laughed Winslow, who played nine years as a tight end for
the Chargers and entered the Pro Football Hall of Fame in 1995.
Tuesday, in his role as commissioner of the Indoor Foortball
League, Winslow helped the Dayton Skyhawks, newest of eight IFL
franchises, drum up interest for their inaugural 12-game season
beginning April 2 at Hara Arena against Green Bay. It's a far cry
from the NFL and Winslow admits he didn't know quite what to think
when approached about the job. But now he's thinking about further
expansion _ to 12 or 16 teams by next year _ and says a cable TV
deal for the league is possible, in part because ``networks are in
dire need of programming.'' (McClelland, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   BASKETBALL
</P>
<P>
   NCAA MENS TOURNAMENT
</P>
<P>
   BKC-LOWSCORES _ Heading into the Sweet 16, an interesting trend
has developed - teams are scoring points at an surprisingly low
rate. In the first 48 games of the tournament, only one team scored
more than 100 points and only five others have scored 90 points. On
the other hand, 15 teams scored in the 50s, three teams scored in
the 40s and SW Missouri State and Wisconsin combined to score only
75 points in a game. Is the low scoring a product of improved
defense or lack of shooters? It is likely a combination of both.
(Barnhart, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BKC-SOUTHADVANCE _ KNOXVILLE _ Unlike the other three regionals,
all of the four teams in the South Regional have a legitimate
chance of advancing to the Final Four. Top seed Auburn is the
likely favorite, but Maryland, St. John's and Ohio State, the
second through fourth seeds, are all capable of winning two more
games. Upsets have not played a major role in the South as the top
four seeds will battle for the regional title. (Wilkinson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BKC-SOUTH-CAPSULES _ KNOXVILLE _ South Regional semifinal
capsules. (Wilkinson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
