<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Thursday, March 18, and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact Stewart Slavin at the Daily News,
(818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   NEWHALL-LAND (Santa Clarita, Calif.) _ Show us the money. That
was the message from some Newhall Land and Farming shareholders to
Thomas Lee, director of the company's board, at Wednesday's annual
unit-holder meeting. The company's share price _ currently well
under analysts' estimates of its value _ took center stage at the
meeting despite the company's record $304 million in revenues and
$1.89 net earnings per unit in 1998. By Jason Takenouchi.
</P>
<P>
   DISNEY-SUIT (Los Angeles) _ A federal judge has given
class-action status to a lawsuit against The Walt Disney Co. over
health benefits for retirees and longtime employees. By Dave
McNary.
</P>
<P>
   TEKELEC-SHARES (Los Angeles) _ Shares of Tekelec fell 26 percent
Wednesday on heavy trading, a day after the maker of telephone
switching devices warned of lower-than-expected revenue growth for
the next six months. By Ben Sullivan.
</P>
