   Ganga, the most prominent IOC member expelled, said he would
accept the IOC decision, but he complained that the investigation
was done hastily and incompletely.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're also thinking at this moment of the African sportsmen;
who will have to realize that our fight faces a new test,'' Ganga
said. ``We have known others, such as racial discrimination,
poverty and indifference. This what we face day to day. Starting
from today this will be the case for injustice and exclusion.''
</P>
<P>
   Ganga, who organized the boycott by African countries of the
1976 Montreal Games, has said in recent days that his case was
politically motivated and that the IOC was targeting its African
members. Three of the six expelled members are Africans.
</P>
<P>
   He refused to elaborate.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
