contact Stewart Slavin at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   HOMEWORK-HEADACHES (Los Angeles) _ Parents who thought their
homework headaches ended when they left school find their
children's assignments are causing them even more grief. A national
study released Wednesday shows half of all parents surveyed said
they had at least one crying, yelling fight with their child in the
past year over homework. By Steve Carney. (Will move in the ``n''
California and ``a'' national news file.)
</P>
<P>
   DEATHROW-HEARING (Los Angeles) _ When convicted cop killer
Kenneth Earl Gay strolled into court, a carefree bounce in his step
loudly rattled the chains clasped around both his ankles. The smile
on the lanky killer's face disturbed Sandra Jackson, the widow of
the hero LAPD officer murdered by Gay in 1983, as she sat in the
front row of the court room. Sixteen years after Jackson's husband
died on the side of a road from six gunshot wounds, Gay has a
chance to save his own life because of a judge's order to hold a
new sentencing hearing. By Greg Gittrich. (Will move in the ``n''
California and ``a'' national news file.)
</P>
</TEXT>
