OUT-WALKER (Bridgeport, Calif.) _ Nevada's East Walker River offers
a tremendous tuneup for the April 24 opening of the Eastern Sierra
trout season, especially when a disco midge pattern is tied at the
end of your fly line. 
By Brett Pauly. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
OUT-OPENER (June Lake, Calif.) _ All major roadside lakes in the
Eastern Sierra are already clear of ice, which is a stark contrast
to last year's trout opener, when Convict Lake remained closed and
Crowley Lake got an 11th thaw three days before opening day. 
By Brett Pauly. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
OUT-WADERS (Los Angeles) _ A look at the various fishing waders and
what's right for which occasion _ neoprene for coldest conditions
and float tubing, lightweight and breathable for shallower water
and warmer conditions and hip waders for shallower water still. 
By Brett Pauly. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
OUT-SALMON (Oxnard, Calif.) _ Review of Saturday's salmon opener
from the decks of the Aquarius out of Port Hueneme Sportfishing.
Will have a breakdown of success rates for the opener, as compared
to the past several years. 
By Brett Pauly. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
OUT-BASICS (San Diego) _ Second installment of ``Barry's Basics''
fishing tips, this time on how to cast safely in a crowd. 
By Barry Brightenburg. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 

