<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Homeowners' fancy turns to projects in the spring
 &HT;    By Susan Harte
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ As spring approaches, many Americans are beginning to
think about sprucing up their homes. In fact, 62 percent of
households are planning some kind of improvement or redecorating
project in 1999, according to the American Express Retail Index.
Consumers will spend an average of $2,747 on everything from
landscaping to room expansion.
</P>
<P>
   But a new study warns homeowners, particularly the elderly,
should use caution in hiring home improvement contractors.
Complaints about home improvement contractors rank second only to
gripes about automobile dealers, according to a study released
Wednesday by the senior citizens advocate group AARP. One in four
consumers reported having a problem with home repair companies,
AARP said.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
