<SLUG> BC-FBN-RICKYS-DAD-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FATHER OF HEISMAN TROPHY WINNER ACCUSED OF EMBEZZLING $20,000 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By STEVE BREWER 
c.1999 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   HOUSTON _ A judge reduced bail from $40,000 to $5,000 Wednesday
for the father of Heisman Trophy winner Ricky Williams, who is
accused of embezzling more than $20,000 from a Houston nursing
home.
</P>
<P>
   At the arraignment in the 351st Criminal District Court,
visiting state District Judge Charles Hearn also appointed defense
attorney James Leitner to represent Errick Lynne Williams Sr., 41.
</P>
<P>
   Prosecutor Terry Jennings and Leitner said they agreed on the
bail reduction. Jennings said he doesn't consider him a flight
risk.
</P>
<P>
   According to jail records, Williams made bail. Attempts to reach
him for comment were unsuccessful.
</P>
<P>
   Leitner declined comment late Wednesday, saying he has had not
had time to review the case.
</P>
<P>
   Jennings said Errick Williams is accused of stealing $20,700
from the Lexington Place Healthcare Center between Oct. 20, 1997,
and Oct. 20, 1998.
</P>
<P>
   Court documents allege that Errick Williams, who was working as
a housekeeping supervisor, created phony documents and timeslips
that showed his wife worked with him, Jennings said. She did not,
but Jennings said Williams collected her checks and cashed them.
</P>
<P>
   Williams' wife, Patricia Maria Williams, 36, has not been
charged.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
XXXX END OF STORY &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
